User Input In Dart:
    Instead of writing hard-coded values, you can give input to the computer. It will make your program more dynamic. You must import the package import 'dart:io'; for user input.

String User Input:
    They are used for storing textual user input. If you want to keep values like somebodyâ€™s name, address, description, etc., you can take string input from the user.

    E.g:        
        import 'dart:io';

        void main() {
        print("Enter name:");
        String? name  = stdin.readLineSync();
        print("The entered name is ${name}");
        }

        Show Output
        Enter name:
        Raj Sharma
        The entered name is Raj Sharma    

Integer User Input:
    You can take integer input to get a numeric value from the user without the decimal point. E.g. 10, 100, -800 etc.

    E.g:        
        import 'dart:io';

        void main() {
        print("Enter number:");
        int? number = int.parse(stdin.readLineSync()!);
        print("The entered number is ${number}");
        }


